The paper deals with the analysis of binary linear codes and their performance under LP or MP decoding, which falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT). The concept of pseudocodewords and their role in decoding is also discussed, which is a topic in IT and probability (cs.ITP). The paper also involves computations and analysis of codes, which could fall under the categories of computational complexity (cs.CC) and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper provides results on the performance of codes under different channels, which could be relevant to the field of signal processing and information theory (cs.SI).
